      "message": "If this object dies, it\u0027ll drop reference to mPullCommand. But, internally, mPullCommand holds a reference to itself in the parallel task it launches.\n\nEventually, it\u0027ll finish the task and then end up calling the callback created here, which will crash.\n\nInstead of a shared_ptr, we really need something that has dual purpose: \n - shared memory management, as it is doing now, with the running parallel task.\n - RAII semantics. If I dropped the token you\u0027d returned, I\u0027ve called cancel() on you, so please don\u0027t call my callbacks anymore.",
